  • Method Details

    • onDataReadyForPayment

      void onDataReadyForPayment​(PaymentService activatedPaymentService, TransactionContext ctx)
      Once the credentials (for CardHolder verification) has been successfully verified, and QR code payment cryptograms have been successfully generated by CPS SDK, MPA will be informed that QRCodeData is available to retrieve. Upon reception of the callback, MPA should call PaymentService.getQRCodeData() to retrieve the QRCodeData.
      Parameters:
      activatedPaymentService - PaymentService
      ctx - TransactionContext

    • onNextTransactionReady

      default void onNextTransactionReady​(DeactivationStatus deactivationStatus, DigitalizedCardStatus digitalizedCardStatus, DigitalizedCard digitalizedCard)
      It is called when payment service deactivation process is finish. Payment service deactivation process will be triggered after QR Code Payment cryptograms have been successfully generated.
      Parameters:
      deactivationStatus - indicate the status of deactivation process DeactivationStatus
      digitalizedCardStatus - indicate the digital card state DigitalizedCardStatus
      digitalizedCard - indicate the digitalized card DigitalizedCard
      Since:
      6.4.0
